Show HN: Beesy: Record Google Meets for Free, No Signups, Download Locally
text:
Happy New Year everyone!

Me and my friend developed this extension to record google meets to the computer directly, there is no cloud dependency, neither do we require any signups, and its free.

We hacked this together in a very small amount of time to check if people would actually use it, so if you find this useful, please let us know so we can improve it.

Also, if you have any feedback/questions/ideas, please do not hesitate and leave a comment.

Ask HN: How Was Your Year in 2022
text:
Hi HN,

I'm curious to hear about everyone's year in 2022! What were some of the highlights of your year? What did you build, achieve, or overcome, either personally or professionally?

Personally, the last year wasn't too bad.

- finished my masters

- took up writing

- worked on my social & comm skills

- started working out

- made lots of good connections

- read quite a few books

- spent quality time with family

- traveled to several places I've been wanting to visit for years

I'd love to hear about some of the things you all have been up to in 2022. What are you most proud of from this past year? Let's share our experiences and accomplishments in the comments below!

Best regards, Rex

AIJack: Security and Privacy Risk Simulator for Machine Learning
text:
AIJack allows you to assess the privacy and security risks of machine learning algorithms such as Model Inversion, Poisoning Attack, Evasion Attack, Free Rider, and Backdoor Attack. AIJack also provides various defense techniques like Differential Privacy, Homomorphic Encryption, and other heuristic approaches. In addition, AIJack provides APIs for many distributed learning schemes like Federated Learning and Split Learning. You can integrate many attack and defense methods into such collaborative learning with a few lines. We currently implement more than 30 state-of-arts methods.

https://github.com/Koukyosyumei/AIJack
